                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><date>Sept 12 5609</date>.</p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Friend,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Yours from <placeName>Baltimore</placeName> I
                                        duly<lb/> received but have been unable to acknowledge it
                                        till<lb/> now. You are more fortunate than I in being able
                                        to<lb/> run about and get a little recreation. I had fully
                                        determined<lb/> to take a short time about the country but
                                        L'homme proposes<lb/> et Dieu disposes. I put it off till
                                        this week when a<lb/> child of <persName>Mr Moss</persName>
                                        dies of cholera and I am fixed, a veritable<lb/>
                                        <add>חשק בצוע</add>. In respect to “the mystery in
                                        connection with a<lb/> lady in
                                                  <placeName>Montreal</placeName>” I have to remark
                                        (the ladies of course<lb/> claiming first attention from we
                                        modern Rabbanim)since<lb/>
                                        <persName>S Selig newman</persName> says in a sermon
                                        preached at the <placeName>London</placeName><lb/> Jewish
                                        free school, “the key <add>?</add> used formerly to be
                                                  <add>והוא מזל זך</add><lb/> but now, complains
                                                  <persName>newman</persName>, perhaps from
                                        actual<lb/> experience poor fellow, “it is <add>והוא ימזל
                                                  זך</add>”, the Lecture<lb/> meant no doubt
                                        pathetically to say we had been <add>קל</add><lb/> enough,
                                        and so allowed the ladies to turn &amp; <add>?</add> at
                                        us<lb/> in the <add>נפעל</add> form.) but to <add>?</add>
                                        from this long<lb/> parenthesis to the “mystery” Did I
                                        mention my lady?<lb/> Certainly not and yet you seem very
                                        anxious to assure<lb/> me that “nothing has ever passed
                                        between us”<add>?</add> who<lb/> are us? You are one, and
                                        who is the second—Oh<lb/> you guilty man! You can't keep a
                                        secret too, I find.<lb/> It is certainly very kind of you to
                                        hope the lady <sic>wont</sic><lb/> refuse a good match, even
                                        myself, in your account after I already</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>wrote you that I would not stand in your way (<add>?</add><lb/> of
                                        me.) But seriously, my respected friend, I do not
                                        presume<lb/> to suggest myself less to dictate to you who
                                        shall be your partner if what<lb/> you tell me will be the
                                        downward course of your life,<lb/> nor <hi rend="underline"
                                                  >when</hi> you shall take her. You are better
                                        competent<lb/> to decide these yourself, I hope that the
                                        little <persName>M<add>?</add></persName><lb/> at banter in
                                        which I have indulged may have been<lb/> not
                                                  <sic>agreable</sic> to you In dismissing (for the
                                        present!)<lb/> this soft subject let me say in justice to
                                        the young<lb/> ladies to whom we have alluded that we
                                        might<lb/> both “go farther and fail worse” As for me, my
                                        dear<lb/> friend, if you find yourself “not in a situation
                                        to<lb/> marry”, I also find myself in such a situation.
                                        You<lb/> only hold your situation for a year longer, I
                                        have<lb/> mine for three only, from present date, Besides
                                        “I<lb/> am not young” and am too busily employed for<lb/>
                                        self and others to think of marriage for a few years<lb/>
                                        and <add>דינינו</add> When I have done a little more (if I
                                        may<lb/> be presumptuous enough to say I have done anything) for<lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">the cause</hi> I shall then be entitled
                                        to spend a few<lb/> hours in the pleasures of domesticity
                                        as<lb/> a reward for my work. You are now fully
                                        entitled<lb/> to such a partial rest, and nothing would
                                        afford<lb/> me greater pleasure than to receive a call from
                                        you<lb/> to introduce you (<add>על ידי חופה וקידושין</add>
                                        into the happy <add>?</add><lb/> At the same time I confess
                                        that it would be a <hi rend="underline">little</hi><lb/>
                                        gratifying to me if I were in a position to ask the same of
                                        you.</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>It was with regret and surprise that I recd your account<lb/> of
                                        the manner in which you as yet find yourself
                                        remunerated<lb/> for your writings, thus, mon ami, le temps
                                        viendra.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">It would give me much pleasure to make the<lb/>
                                        acquaintance of Mrs as also of <persName>Mr Cohen</persName>
                                        of <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>,<lb/> persons of whom
                                        fame speaks so favorably here, I gave<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mrs <sic>Cohens</sic></persName> message to
                                                  <persName>Mrs <add>?</add> Solomons</persName>,
                                                  <persName>Mrs S</persName> desires<lb/> me to ask
                                        you when you are going to <placeName>New Orleans</placeName><lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr Touro</persName> of that place is related to
                                        them, and you<lb/> know how it is when we have rich
                                        relations, we like<lb/> to know something of their
                                        whereabouts. She would<lb/> also like to know where
                                                  <persName>Mr Touro</persName> is living in
                                                  <placeName>New Orleans</placeName><lb/> I gave
                                        your message to <persName>Mr Jacob Joseph</persName>, but as
                                        his<lb/> brother <persName>Pepe</persName> and sister
                                                  <persName>Esther</persName> are in your city
                                        you<lb/> can make your own explanations to the <add>אם סוד
                                                  דעתיך</add></p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">The Occident for <date>September</date> has not
                                        arrived yet<lb/> so cannot say anything on matters literary,
                                        The<lb/> articles on the Jews of
                                                  <placeName>Persia</placeName> I shall not be able to<lb/>
                                        <sic>commense</sic>
                                        <sic>untill</sic> after <add>סוכות</add>. It is seldom or
                                        never<lb/> that I stipulate for special time for <del>the
                                                  Oc</del> my articles<lb/> but in the case of
                                        sermons I do, I have published<lb/> scarcely other than
                                        occasional sermons which<lb/> loose their interest and
                                        effect when the cause or<lb/> event they speak upon is part.
                                        Thus my<lb/> Sermon on the cholera would have been much
                                        more<lb/> seasonable reading for your readers while the<lb/>
                                        epidemic prevailed, and might have been to me<lb/> more
                                        effect, so a sermon I sent you for</p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p><add>שנת ברכה והצלחה</add> was published a “day after the fair” In
                                        future I must<lb/> trouble you to let me know when I send a
                                        sermon whether<lb/> it can be published at the time required
                                        as I would then<lb/> prefer its not being published at all
                                        if not at the<lb/> specified time.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">You have been made aware long before this of
                                        the<lb/> visit of <persName>Dr Raphael</persName> and
                                                  <persName>Dr Isaacs</persName> to the
                                                  <placeName>United States</placeName>.<lb/> The
                                        latter <add>?</add> avowedly to seek for a situation in
                                                  <placeName>America</placeName><lb/> the former to
                                        make a little fortune by lecturing<lb/> and as the chronicle
                                        tells us will no doubt be<lb/> permanently engaged in the
                                                  <placeName>United States</placeName>. I hope<lb/>
                                        both these gentlemen for their sakes will not find<lb/>
                                        themselves mistaken. I am not sanguine enough<lb/> of you
                                        Yankee Israelites to believe that <persName>Dr
                                                  Raphael</persName><lb/> will find a better
                                        situation than the one he filled<lb/> at
                                                  <placeName>Birmingham</placeName> &amp; which
                                        yielded him £500 sterling<lb/> It would be uncharitable to
                                                  <hi rend="underline">believe</hi> all that is
                                        said<lb/> of <persName>Mr D Isaacs</persName>, but he was
                                        spoke of both in<lb/>
                                        <placeName>London</placeName> and elsewhere as possessing a
                                        temper not at all<lb/> likely to <add>?</add> success. Let
                                        me hear what you<lb/> think of the contemplated visits. I
                                        have now written<lb/> your <add>?</add> fully and must
                                        therefore close. Wishing<lb/> you many happy returns of the
                                        coming <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> and praying that the coming
                                        year may be to<lb/> you <add>Hebrew</add></p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">I am dear Friend</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">Yours truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName>
                              </p>
